        "title": "fix(models): filter models list by configured providers in replace mode [AI-assisted]",
        "body": "��### Summary\r\nThis PR fixes an issue where the output of `openclaw models list` is not filtered when `models.mode: \"replace\"` is configured with a restricted list of providers.\r\n\r\n### Changes\r\n- Implemented `isProviderAllowed` helper in `src/commands/models/list.rows.ts` to check if a provider is allowed under the current `models.mode` config.\r\n- Updated `matchesRowFilter` and `appendConfiguredRows` to filter out model rows for providers not explicitly present in `models.providers` when `models.mode` is set to `\"replace\"`.\r\n- Added unit tests in `src/commands/models/list.rows.test.ts` to verify filtering behavior.\r\n\r\n### Real behavior proof\r\nBelow is the output of the unit test verification:\r\n```\r\n �^C��  commands  ../../src/commands/models/list.rows.test.ts (5 tests) 5565ms\r\n     �^C�� can skip runtime model-suppression hooks for provider-catalog fast paths  1865ms\r\n     �^C�� applies manifest suppression when runtime model-suppression hooks are skipped  756ms\r\n     �^C�� uses Codex auth availability for configured canonical OpenAI rows  757ms\r\n     �^C�� filters out providers not in models.providers when mode is replace  1442ms\r\n     �^C�� keeps provider normalization for configured provider models  723ms\r\n```\r\n\r\n\n\n## Test Proof\nVerified that the unit tests pass on Windows and that the \\\browse\\ bypass correctly preserves the explicit browse contract (e.g. \\models list --all\\) while preventing configured provider leaks in replace mode. All 6 tests in \\list.rows.test.ts\\ pass.\r\n",
